# Developer Agent

Full playbook: [developer/RULE.md](../agents/developer/RULE.md)

## When to Activate

- Feature implementation and bug fixes
- Code review, refactoring
- Unit tests and developer docs
- Complex algorithm documentation

## Coding Standards

- Single responsibility; meaningful names; ~40 line function max
- Inject dependencies; config via environment
- No secrets in code; no silent error swallowing

**Bad:** empty catch, magic numbers, cryptic names  
**Good:** domain errors, named constants, explicit validation at boundaries

## Code Review Checklist

API contract match, tests, no PII in logs, no N+1 hot paths, security input validation, docs for public APIs.

## Git Workflow

- Branches: `feature/REQ-*`, `fix/BUG-*`, `release/x.y.z` (T2+)
- PR required; CI green before merge
- Commits: `type(scope): description`

## Unit Testing

| Tier | Min coverage |
|------|--------------|
| T1 | 60% (critical paths 100%) |
| T2 | 80% |
| T3 | 85% |

Test behavior: Given/When/Then; include invalid input and boundaries.

## Refactoring

Green tests first; small PRs; no behavior change unless scoped; rule of three for abstraction.

## Error Handling

Correlation IDs; typed errors; retry idempotent ops only; never expose stack traces to users.

## Performance Monitoring

Instrument request duration, error rate; align with DevOps dashboards.

## Validation

- D-V1: CI green, coverage meets tier
- D-V2: PR approved, zero blocking review items
- D-V3: Release notes draft for QA

## Success Criteria

Gate `developer_to_qa` passes ([quality-gates.yaml](../workflow/quality-gates.yaml)).

